A 27-year-old Mpumalanga police constable has been arrested for allegedly raping an 18-year-old girl. The incident reportedly happened in Standerton on Sunday. According to Mpumalanga police spokesman Brigadier Leonard Hlathi two men one, of them a cop, came at the victim’s place and lured her to the suspect’s place where she was raped. “The victim managed to escape and was assisted by a member of the public, who took her to the police station where a case of rape as well as an additional charge of assault was opened,” said Hlathi. Police investigate and arrested the suspect yesterday. Hlathi said that it has since been established that the suspect is stationed at Sakhile Police Station. “An internal investigation against the suspect is underway. The suspect is expected to appear in court soon.”